## 3. Key Technical Concepts:

- **HashMap**: Hash table implementation of Map interface, O(1) average time complexity
- **Abstract classes vs Interfaces**: Single vs multiple inheritance, instance variables vs constants
- **AbstractMap<K,V>**: Skeletal implementation providing default methods for Map implementations
- **Map.Entry interface**: Nested interface representing key-value pairs
- **Node structure**: Internal class with fields (hash, key, value, next)
- **Hashing algorithm**: Two-step process - key.hashCode() then XOR with (hashCode >>> 16)
- **Bucket indexing**: Formula (n-1) & hash where n is capacity (power of 2)
- **Collision handling**: Separate chaining using linked lists (Java 7) or trees (Java 8+)
- **Treeification**: Conversion from linked list to Red-Black Tree when bucket size > 8 and capacity >= 64
- **Load factor**: Default 0.75, determines when to resize
- **Capacity**: Default 16, always power of 2, doubles on resize
- **Threshold**: capacity * loadFactor, triggers resize when exceeded
- **Rehashing**: O(n) operation to redistribute entries after capacity doubles
- **hashCode() and equals() contract**: If a.equals(b) then a.hashCode() == b.hashCode()
- **Bitwise operators**: Left shift (<<), right shift (>>), unsigned right shift (>>>), AND (&)
- **Fail-fast iterators**: Throw ConcurrentModificationException on concurrent modification
- **Thread safety**: HashMap is not thread-safe, use ConcurrentHashMap or Collections.synchronizedMap()
- **Time complexity**: O(1) average for get/put, O(log n) worst case in Java 8+ (with trees)

